<h1 id="appA">Appendix A: Glossary of RTSA Terms</h1>

<p>The full glossary of 80+ terms is available in the appendices Markdown file. Highlights here include the most-referenced terms across the book.</p>

<p><span class="glossary-term">RTBW (Real-Time Bandwidth)</span> - Width of spectrum that an RTSA digitizes simultaneously with no time gaps.</p>
<p><span class="glossary-term">POI (Probability of Intercept)</span> - Minimum signal duration captured with near certainty by an analyzer. SPECTRAN V6 PLUS achieves 10 ns POI.</p>
<p><span class="glossary-term">SigMF</span> - Open standard for I/Q file metadata; JSON sidecar paired with raw data file.</p>
<p><span class="glossary-term">PDW (Pulse Descriptor Word)</span> - Fixed-format record describing a single pulse: TOA, PW, frequency, amplitude.</p>
<p><span class="glossary-term">EVM (Error Vector Magnitude)</span> - RMS error between received and ideal constellation points, normalized by reference power.</p>
<p><span class="glossary-term">DRFM (Digital Radio Frequency Memory)</span> - EW jammer that captures, modifies, and retransmits incoming victim signals.</p>
<p><span class="glossary-term">IsoLOG 3D DF</span> - Aaronia's direction-finding antenna family with sectored arrays and elevation capability. 16 sectors, 32 antennas, 400 MHz to 40 GHz, 8 microsecond bearing.</p>
<p><span class="glossary-term">SPECTRAN V6 PLUS</span> - Aaronia's flagship USB real-time spectrum analyzer family.</p>
<p><span class="glossary-term">Wrapped Spectrum</span> - Aaronia patented display that stacks frequency axis across multiple lines for high-resolution wide-span monitoring.</p>

<p><em>For the full 80+ term glossary, see the Markdown source in /book/appendices/APPENDICES-A-F.md.</em></p>

<h1 id="appB">Appendix B: Math Reference</h1>

<h2>Fourier Transform</h2>

<p><strong>DFT:</strong></p>
<div class="math-display">$$X[k] = \sum_{n=0}^{N-1} x[n] e^{-j 2\pi k n / N}$$</div>

<p><strong>Bin frequency:</strong> $f_k = k \cdot f_s / N$. <strong>RBW:</strong> $\Delta f = f_s / N$.</p>

<h2>Window Functions</h2>

<table>
<thead><tr><th>Window</th><th>ENBW factor</th><th>Highest sidelobe (dB)</th><th>Main lobe -3 dB (bins)</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Rectangular</td><td>1.00</td><td>-13</td><td>0.89</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hann</td><td>1.50</td><td>-32</td><td>1.44</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hamming</td><td>1.36</td><td>-43</td><td>1.30</td></tr>
<tr><td>Blackman</td><td>1.73</td><td>-58</td><td>1.68</td></tr>
<tr><td>Blackman-Harris</td><td>2.00</td><td>-92</td><td>1.90</td></tr>
<tr><td>Flat-top</td><td>3.77</td><td>-88</td><td>3.86</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h2>POI Formula (Swept Analyzer)</h2>

<div class="math-display">$$P_{\text{intercept}} = \frac{t_{\text{dwell}} + t_b}{T_{\text{sweep}}}$$ where $$t_{\text{dwell}} = \frac{B_{IF} \cdot T_{\text{sweep}}}{\Delta f}$$</div>

<h2>Friis Noise Formula</h2>

<div class="math-display">$$F_{\text{total}} = F_1 + \frac{F_2 - 1}{G_1} + \frac{F_3 - 1}{G_1 G_2} + \cdots$$</div>

<h2>EVM</h2>

<div class="math-display">$$\text{EVM}_{rms} = \sqrt{\frac{\frac{1}{N} \sum_n |\vec{e}[n]|^2}{P_{\text{ref}}}}$$</div>

<h2>IIP3 / IM3</h2>

<div class="math-display">$$P_{IM3} = 3P - 2 \cdot P_{IIP3}$$</div>

<h2>Decibel Quick Reference</h2>

<table>
<thead><tr><th>Linear ratio</th><th>dB (power)</th><th>dB (voltage)</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>0.001</td><td>-30</td><td>-60</td></tr>
<tr><td>0.1</td><td>-10</td><td>-20</td></tr>
<tr><td>0.5</td><td>-3</td><td>-6</td></tr>
<tr><td>1</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr>
<tr><td>2</td><td>+3</td><td>+6</td></tr>
<tr><td>10</td><td>+10</td><td>+20</td></tr>
<tr><td>100</td><td>+20</td><td>+40</td></tr>
<tr><td>1000</td><td>+30</td><td>+60</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

