<h1 id="appI">Appendix I: Standards and Regulatory Quick Reference</h1>

<h2>US FCC Parts</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Part 15:</strong> Unlicensed RF devices (ISM, U-NII)</li>
<li><strong>Part 22, 24, 27:</strong> Cellular and PCS</li>
<li><strong>Part 73, 74:</strong> Broadcast and aux broadcast</li>
<li><strong>Part 90:</strong> Land mobile radio (public safety)</li>
<li><strong>Part 95:</strong> Personal radio (CB, FRS, GMRS)</li>
<li><strong>Part 96:</strong> CBRS spectrum sharing (3.5 GHz)</li>
<li><strong>Part 97:</strong> Amateur radio</li>
</ul>

<h2>ETSI EN Standards (Europe)</h2>
<ul>
<li>EN 300 220: Short-range devices (25 MHz - 1 GHz)</li>
<li>EN 301 893: 5 GHz Wi-Fi</li>
<li>EN 302 208: RFID</li>
<li>EN 303 645: IoT cybersecurity</li>
</ul>

<h2>3GPP (Cellular)</h2>
<ul>
<li>TS 38.xxx: 5G NR (TS 38.101 UE, 38.104 BS, 38.211-214 PHY)</li>
<li>TS 36.xxx: LTE</li>
<li>TR 38.913: 5G requirements</li>
</ul>

<h2>MIL-STD / Aerospace</h2>
<ul>
<li>MIL-STD-461: EMI/EMC for military equipment</li>
<li>MIL-STD-188: Telecommunications</li>
<li>MIL-STD-810: Environmental engineering</li>
<li>DO-160 (RTCA): Avionics environmental</li>
<li>DO-178 / DO-254: Software / hardware safety for avionics</li>
</ul>

<h2>ITU-R Recommendations</h2>
<ul>
<li>ITU-R SM.1880: Spectrum monitoring evolution</li>
<li>ITU-R SM.443: Direction finding</li>
<li>ITU-R SM.1538: Methods of measurement of radio noise</li>
</ul>

<h2>IEEE 802.11 Wi-Fi</h2>
<ul>
<li>802.11ac: Wi-Fi 5</li>
<li>802.11ax: Wi-Fi 6 / 6E (1024-QAM, OFDMA, 6 GHz)</li>
<li>802.11be: Wi-Fi 7 (320 MHz channels, 4096-QAM, MLO)</li>
<li>802.11bn: Wi-Fi 8 (in development)</li>
</ul>

<h1 id="appJ">Appendix J: Tools, Software, and Datasets</h1>

<h2>Open-Source Signal Processing</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>GNU Radio:</strong> de facto open-standard SDR framework</li>
<li><strong>scikit-rf:</strong> Python RF/microwave network analysis</li>
<li><strong>scipy.signal:</strong> general DSP within scientific Python</li>
<li><strong>NumPy:</strong> foundational array math</li>
<li><strong>MATLAB Signal Processing Toolbox:</strong> commercial</li>
<li><strong>Octave:</strong> free MATLAB-compatible alternative</li>
</ul>

<h2>SDR Control Software</h2>
<ul>
<li>GQRX (multi-SDR), SDR# / SDRSharp (Windows), SDR Console, CubicSDR (cross-platform), OpenWebRX (web-based)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Specialized Analysis Tools</h2>
<ul>
<li>Inspectrum (graphical I/Q analysis)</li>
<li>Universal Radio Hacker (protocol reverse engineering)</li>
<li>rtl_433 (433/315/868/915 MHz device decoding)</li>
<li>Wireshark with Bluetooth/Wi-Fi plugins</li>
</ul>

<h2>SigMF Ecosystem</h2>
<p>Open standard for I/Q metadata. Python <code>sigmf</code> package, supported by GNU Radio, scikit-rf, RTSA Suite PRO, and most modern tools.</p>

<h2>Aaronia RTSA Suite PRO</h2>
<ul>
<li>Block-based pipeline editor</li>
<li>Custom triggers and FMTs</li>
<li>AI classification plugins</li>
<li>Modulation-specific demodulators</li>
<li>Python and C++ scripting hooks</li>
<li>KML / KMZ / GeoJSON / NMEA / MQTT / REST export</li>
</ul>

<h2>Public Datasets</h2>
<ul>
<li>DARPA Spectrum Collaboration Challenge</li>
<li>RadioML 2018 / 2024 datasets</li>
<li>DeepSig RFML Dataset</li>
<li>Galaxy Radio Survey archives</li>
<li>ETSI test vector sets</li>
</ul>

